      "commit_id": null,
      "commit_url": null,
      "created_at": "2026-03-19T07:23:55Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-19T07:24:47Z",
      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "I had a look, and it seems to be caused by unclean shutdown in `Socks5Server`. Incoming connections are handled in separate threads, but the thread handles are not stored and they are never joined. As a result, it can happen that `stop()` returns (it unblocks the accepting thread and joins that), but a connection handler thread is still active.\nIf after stopping the socks server -- like in the test case -- the node is closed, connection errors can happen in the still-running background thread.\nWorking on a fix.",
